# MiYo Tomo — {{INSTANCE_NAME}}

AI-assisted PKM workflows for Obsidian. All vault access goes through Kado MCP.

## Context

@.claude/rules/project-context.md

For vault structure (MOCs, tags, frontmatter, folder layout), see `config/vault-config.yaml`
(machine-readable source of truth) and `config/vault-config.md` (human-readable summary,
updated by `/explore-vault`).

For Kado connection details, see `config/kado-config.md` (human-readable) and `.mcp.json`
(machine-readable; holds the bearer token).

## Key Commands

- /tomo-setup    — post-install setup wizard (run first)
- /inbox         — analyse inbox and generate instruction set
- /execute       — execute an approved instruction set
- /explore-vault — standalone vault rescan (normally invoked by /tomo-setup)

## Rules

- ALWAYS use Plan Mode before any task touching more than 2 vault files
- NEVER modify vault files without an approved instruction set
- Propose changes as instruction set entries — never execute directly
- Update config/vault-config.md (and vault-config.yaml) when you discover new vault structure
- Commit after every completed task

## Vault Conventions (user-specific)

Consult these only when the active task matches their topic. These are vault-specific
behavioral rules that override framework defaults:

- For tag-selection rules (which `type/*` per note, template-vs-tag precedence) → see `config/user-rules/tagging.md`
- For destination rules (where resources go, which targets get MOC links) → see `config/user-rules/destinations.md`
- For template-selection rules per note type → see `config/user-rules/templates.md`

Add additional topic files under `config/user-rules/` and reference them here as
your conventions grow. See `config/user-rules/README.md` for the pattern.

